vironment = environment\\n        self.position = (random.randint(0, environment.map_size - 1), random.randint(0, environment.map_size - 1))\\n\\n    def act(self):\\n        # Define the agent\'s action\\n        # For simplicity, let\'s move the agent randomly\\n        self.position = (random.randint(0, self.environment.map_size - 1), random.randint(0, self.environment.map_size - 1))\\n\\nif __name__ == \\"__main__\\":\\n    game = GameEnvironment(map_size=10)\\n    for _ in range(10):\\n        game.update()\\n        game.render()\\n"\n}\n```\n\nThis code provides a basic structure for the `Team_Tactics` game, including a `GameEnvironment` class to manage the game state and an `Agent` class to represent the AI agents. The `GameEnvironment` initializes the game with flags, bases, and agents, and the `Agent` class defines a simple random movement action. The `main` block creates a game instance and runs a few updates to demonstrate the game\'s functionality. This framework can be expanded and refined in subsequent steps.', role='assistant', tool_calls=None, function_call=None, provider_specific_fields=None)
